main event: A witness in Oxford, Ohio spotted three reddish-white objects in the sky on November 5, 1965.
interesting points: The witness contacted the control center to inquire if the objects were detected on radar, but the center had no record of any unusual activity in the area.
The objects were described as moving at a tremendous speed, first one and then the other, and were much larger than stars.
The objects were circular in shape and extremely bright, appearing to be 50 to 70 degrees from where the witness stood.
The objects moved in a straight line with no deviation.
The witness provided a drawing of the observed objects.
sighted object: three reddish-white objects in the sky
photographs: yes, the report includes a drawing of the observed objects
